The United States congratulates Afghanistan on the completion of the second round of voting in their presidential elections. These elections are seen as a significant step forward for the country's democratic progress. The courage and determination of the Afghan people in participating and making their voices heard is recognized and praised. The United States commends the voters, electoral bodies, and security forces for their commitment to the democratic process. The focus now shifts to the work of the electoral commissions in the coming weeks. The United States looks forward to working with the next government chosen by the Afghan people, as they continue the challenging task of building a democracy. The statement also reiterates the United States' commitment to supporting Afghanistan beyond 2014, stating that while the future of Afghanistan must be decided by Afghans, the United States will continue to provide assistance in their efforts.